            "title": "Kuaishou's Kling AI Video-Generation Tool Could Maintain Lead -- Market Talk",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n     0350 GMT - Kuaishou's Kling AI could maintain its leading position among AI video-generation models after its recent momentum, Citi analysts say in a research note. Citi updates its model to factor in the decent momentum of Kling, raising its target price to HK$95.00 from HK$88.00. Kling's latest model, launched in December, with a new function dubbed \"motion control,\" has gained traction in several countries. Kuaishou's 4Q overall revenue could grow 9.6% to 38.8 billion yuan, with gross profit margin likely rising to 55.5%, the analysts say. Citi expects Kuaishou's livestreaming e-commerce business growth to continue outpacing traditional e-commerce platforms in 2026. Shares are last 1.2% higher at HK$83.30. (sherry.qin@wsj.com) </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  01-28-26 2305ET</p></div>",
            "link": "https://hk.marketscreener.com/news/kuaishou-s-kling-ai-video-generation-tool-could-maintain-lead-market-talk-ce7e5bdeda8cf422",
            "pub_date": "2026-01-29 12:08:28",
            "source": "marketscreener",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
        },
